==English==
===Adjective===
'''frequentative'''

# Adjective describing a Latin verb formed from the past participle of another verb.  The new verb is generally first conjugation.

====Example====
In this example, two new verbs developed from the original verb '''[[canere]]''', ''sing'': first '''cantus''' produced '''cantare''', and then '''cantatus''' produced '''cantitare''', ''chant'' or ''sing repetitively''.<br>
